# TellStick Local – App for Home Assistant

[![Release Candidate][rc-shield]][repo]
![Project Maintenance][maintenance-shield]

Local TellStick Duo support for Home Assistant – no cloud, no Telldus Live.

## About

This app runs the Telldus `telldusd` daemon inside a Docker container managed by
the HAOS Supervisor and exposes it over TCP so the **TellStick Local** integration
can create HA entities for your 433 MHz devices.

It exists because HAOS only allows USB hardware passthrough to Supervisor-managed
containers. The app handles the hardware; the integration handles everything in
the HA UI.

